        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51487",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Interestingly, you can do the following fine:\r\n{code}\r\n$container += 1;\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nConsidering that internally we're using an ArrayObject, the liklihood of getting this to work with increment and decrement operators is pretty slim. However, since increment\/decrement on assignment works fine, I'd argue we should simply document those use cases.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-07-30T20:55:50.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-07-30T20:55:50.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51488",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Updating issue type to \"documentation task\".",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-07-30T20:56:22.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-07-30T20:56:22.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51492",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=demiankatz",
                        "name": "demiankatz",
                        "displayName": "Demian Katz",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Increment\/decrement was just the simplest use case I could think of that caused a problem.  Possibly more serious is the problem of appending to existing arrays:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n    public function testContainerAllowsArrayModificationOfArrays()\r\n    {\r\n        $this->container['foo'] = array();\r\n        $this->assertEquals(0, count($this->container['foo']));\r\n        $this->container['foo'][] = 'bar';\r\n        $this->assertEquals(1, count($this->container['foo']));\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    public function testContainerAllowsObjectModificationOfArrays()\r\n    {\r\n        $this->container->foo = array();\r\n        $this->assertEquals(0, count($this->container->foo));\r\n        $this->container->foo[] = 'bar';\r\n        $this->assertEquals(1, count($this->container->foo));\r\n    }\r\n{code}\r\n\r\n(These trigger errors equivalent to the ones listed in the ticket above).\r\n\r\nI agree that {code}$container += 1{code} is a relatively painless substitute for {code}$container++{code} (though I still think it's likely to cause bugs and confusion, even if documented).  However, it's even less desirable to be forced to replace {code}$container[] = 'bar'{code} with {code}$container = $container + array('bar'){code}.  (You can't use += in this context -- it yields an \"Unsupported operand types\" fatal error).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=demiankatz",
                        "name": "demiankatz",
                        "displayName": "Demian Katz",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-07-31T12:36:59.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-07-31T12:37:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51493",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Right, but, again, because it's an ArrayObject implementation internally, you _can_ do this:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n$container->foo->append('bar');\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nAs such, I still feel this falls into a documentation issue -- we need to clarify that the container and its members follows ArrayObject behavior, which means you have to treat it as such when using it.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-07-31T13:22:05.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-07-31T13:22:05.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51495",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=demiankatz",
                        "name": "demiankatz",
                        "displayName": "Demian Katz",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Makes sense -- thanks for the clarification.  (I'm still not totally comfortable with ArrayObject behavior, but that's not ZF's problem!).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=demiankatz",
                        "name": "demiankatz",
                        "displayName": "Demian Katz",
                        "active": true
                    },
